Scout4all Data Collection / Privacy

This software may collect anonymous match statistics to improve features and analytics.

- No personal data is collected (player names, team names, locations are never transmitted).  
- Player identifiers are local to your computer and cannot be linked to real individuals.  
- Data is used only for software improvement and analytics.  

You can disable data collection at any time from the program settings.  
By using this software, you acknowledge that anonymous statistics may be collected automatically.

This software complies with EU GDPR (Regulation 2016/679) principles, even though no personal data is collected.
